longName: The Kansai Electric Power Company, Incorporated
longBusinessSummary: The Kansai Electric Power Company, Incorporated engages in electric power, gas supply, heat supply, and telecommunication businesses in Japan. The company operates through Electric Power, Gas/Other Energies, IT/Communications, and Real Estate segments. The company generates power from thermal, hydropower, wind, biomass, and nuclear power generation facilities. It also offers IT services for households and business firms, including optical fiber internet, optical fiber telephone, and optical fiber television; real estate services, such as leasing, condominium sales, property management, leisure, etc.; and specific services, such as home security, healthcare, etc. for individuals, and call center and staffing services, etc. for businesses. The company serves residential, commercial, and industrial customers. The Kansai Electric Power Company, Incorporated was founded in 1951 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan.
